# Angular Template Control Flow

- Use `@if`, `@for`, and `@switch` in templates.
- Do not introduce `*ngIf`, `*ngFor`, or `*ngSwitch` in new or edited code.
- Include `track` expressions for `@for` whenever a stable identifier exists.
- Keep conditional rendering in template syntax, not by generating HTML strings.

## Examples

- ✅ `@for (item of items(); track item.id) { ... }`
- ❌ `<div *ngFor="let item of items">...</div>`
